OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCardiac arrest:            
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FDefibrillator thefts       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F'risking lives'            
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Lives are being put at risk by people  
OL,6, who steal and vandalise defibrillators,
OL,7, the Welsh Ambulance Trust has said.    
OL,9,FIt said at least eight had been stolen 
OL,10,For damaged in the past 12 months.      
OL,12,FCardiac arrest survivor Alan Mathias   
OL,13,Fsaid it was "just incredible" people   
OL,14,Fwould target the life-saving equipment.
OL,16,FFewer than 5% of people survive a      
OL,17,Fcardiac arrest outside hospital but    
OL,18,Fthat rises to 70% if a defibrillator is
OL,19,Fused within three minutes, according to
OL,20,FSt John Ambulance Cymru.               
